## Summary of New Concepts and Scope

The brief introduces three new kit contribution field types:

| Field | Contributed by | Consumed by | Namespace-qualified? |
|-------|---------------|-------------|---------------------|
| `writTypes` | Kit | Clerk | No (user-facing names) |
| `rigTemplates` | Kit | Spider | Yes (`pluginId.templateName`) |
| `rigTemplateMappings` | Kit | Spider | No (writ type names are user-facing) |

Override semantics at all three layers: config wins, kit contribution is skipped/lower-priority when config declares the same name.

The "plug-and-play" story requires all three contributions to work together: a kit contributes a writ type (Clerk registers it), a rig template (Spider registers it as `pluginId.name`), and a mapping (Spider maps the writ type to the template). Installing the plugin is sufficient — no guild.json changes required.

The `lookupTemplate` function is the critical seam where all three contribution types converge. It must consult:
1. Config-defined `rigTemplateMappings` (new field)
2. Config-defined `rigTemplates` direct key lookup (existing behavior, backwards compat)
3. Kit-contributed `rigTemplateMappings`
4. `'default'` key in the merged template registry
